if you were feeling low or if you were feeling low or bitter what song would suit your mood mine would be miss otis regrets miss otis regrets is a song in the blues style and porter's wry take on some common lyrical subject matter of the genre telling the tale of a woman who comes to a bad end after an encounter with a man but porter's peculiar twist is that miss otis is a polite society lady and the story of her last evening is told by her servant after miss otis has met her demise in a few compact lines the servant reveals how after being seduced and then abandoned miss otis hunted down and shot her seducer was arrested taken from the jail by a mob and hanged the servant conveys miss otis's final polite apologetic words to her friends miss otis regrets she's unable to lunch today minutes ago source wikipedia rp depends on what kind of bitter when i'm lonely i love i'll be seeing you by billie holiday The Temptations God Emperor of Dune Knots Landing Cole Porter Blood on the Tracks Sin City Sydney Riot of 1879 Otis Redding Sam Cooke Wyatt Earp Cliff Richard One Tree Hill (TV series) EastEnders Diana Ross The Freewheelin' Bob Dylan The Grim Adventures of Billy and Mandy Shaggy dog story Billy Joel Just My Imagination (Running Away with Me) Anne Boleyn Ella Fitzgerald Marilyn Monroe John Lennon Scenes from a Memory Days of our Lives Western (genre) Aida (musical) Nancy Witcher Astor Samples of music from the United States Spidey Super Stories American Idiot Humphrey Bogart Aretha Franklin Audrey Hepburn Rock Follies Johnny Cash Henry: Portrait Of A Serial Killer Rhythm and blues George Costanza Blonde on Blonde Harry Potter and the Prisoner of Azkaban The Emancipation of Mimi The Times They Are A-Changin' Paul Is Dead Tupac Shakur Forty-seven Ronin The Dark Knight Returns American Civil Rights Movement (1955-1968) The Beatles discography The Rock and Roll Hall of Fame's 500 Songs that Shaped Rock and Roll The Subtle Knife Steely Dan Parsifal Lynching in the United St